text: The voiceless bilabial nasal is a type of consonant. It is a rare sound. The letter for this sound in the International Phonetic Alphabet is ⟨⟩. The X-SAMPA symbol for this sound is `⟨m_0⟩`. The English language does not have the sound. ==Features== Features of the voiceless alveolar trill: ==Examples== Language Language Word IPA Meaning Burmese Burmese /hma: 'notice' Central Alaskan Yup'ik Central Alaskan Yup'ik 'to the servant' Estonian Estonian 'cow' French French 'prism' Hmong Hmong 'Hmong' Icelandic Icelandic 'hemp' Jalapa Mazatec Jalapa Mazatec hma 'black' Kildin Sami Kildin Sami /ljeehmhmk 'strap' Muscogee Muscogee 'bell' Ukrainian /ritm 'rhythm' Washo Washo 'he's hiding' Welsh Welsh 'my head' Xumi Lower 'medicine' Upper Yi Language Yi Language 'Cuckoo Tree' == Notes == == References == * * * * * * * * Category:Consonants
